        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Confidentiality Opportunities for Peer Support Counseling Act or the COPS Counseling Act</b></p> <p>This bill sets forth requirements related to peer support counseling programs. A peer support counseling program is a program provided by a law enforcement agency that provides counseling services from a peer support specialist to a law enforcement officer of the agency.</p> <p>Among other things, the bill does the following:</p> <ul> <li>generally prohibits the disclosure of the contents of a peer support communication, and</li> <li>requires the Department of Justice to develop best practices and professional standards for peer support counseling programs.</li> </ul>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
